COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 858, L.D. 1323
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve and adds an emergency preamble and
33 emergency clause. The amendment requires the Department of Agriculture, Conservation
44 and Forestry, Board of Pesticides Control to study the impact of neonicotinoids, including
55 neonicotinoid-treated seeds, on pollinators, humans and the environment. The amendment
66 requires the board to solicit feedback regarding ideas and insights on the topic of the study
77 from the public, stakeholders and interested parties through either a public hearing or a
88 request for information document. The amendment requires the board to submit a
99 preliminary report and a final report with findings and recommendations relating to the
1100 subject matter of the study to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having
1111 jurisdiction over agricultural matters. The amendment also adds an appropriations and
1122 allocations section.
